Retrieve from an image
----------------------
The source and legal files are outside the project bind mount and remain in
every distributed runtime image:

  docker create --name herdr-source IMAGE
  docker cp herdr-source:/usr/share/src/herdr/herdr-0.7.4-corresponding-source.tar.gz .
  docker cp herdr-source:/usr/share/src/herdr/herdr-0.7.4-corresponding-source.tar.gz.sha256 .
  docker cp herdr-source:/usr/share/doc/herdr/LICENSE ./herdr-0.7.4-LICENSE
  docker cp herdr-source:/usr/share/doc/herdr/NOTICE ./herdr-0.7.4-NOTICE
  docker cp herdr-source:/usr/share/doc/herdr/SOURCE-OFFER ./herdr-0.7.4-SOURCE-OFFER
  docker rm herdr-source
  sha256sum -c herdr-0.7.4-corresponding-source.tar.gz.sha256

Replace IMAGE with the exact Open Harness image reference you received.

Retrieve from a tagged Open Harness release
-------------------------------------------
Each tagged Open Harness release that contains Herdr v0.7.4 attaches:

  herdr-0.7.4-corresponding-source.tar.gz
  herdr-0.7.4-corresponding-source.tar.gz.sha256
  herdr-0.7.4-LICENSE
  herdr-0.7.4-NOTICE
  herdr-0.7.4-SOURCE-OFFER

Use the image's dev.openharness.herdr.source.url label to obtain the direct
release-asset URL. The URL is checksum-verifiable using the adjacent checksum
and the dev.openharness.herdr.source.sha256 label; it is not described as an
immutable storage guarantee:

  docker image inspect IMAGE --format \
    '{{ index .Config.Labels "dev.openharness.herdr.source.url" }}'

The verified upstream commit snapshot used as the source input is:
  https://codeload.github.com/ogulcancelik/herdr/tar.gz/50aaa2ec046ee26ff407c20f49de496f522512a8

Source contents and build scope
-------------------------------
The bundle contains the exact upstream repository tree for the commit above,
renamed herdr-0.7.4, including Cargo.lock, Cargo.toml, build.rs, and upstream's
vendored patched portable-pty code. Open Harness has not modified those files.
For conservative completeness, the bundle also includes locked Rust registry
and Git dependency sources under vendor/cargo, generated with Cargo 1.96.1 by:

  cargo vendor --locked --versioned-dirs vendor/cargo

It also includes exactly the 36 Zig package-source directories named by
vendor/libghostty-vt/build.zig.zon.json under vendor/zig-global-cache/p. They
are fetched with Zig 0.15.2, Python 3 validates the exact directory-name set,
and the generated local cache and build-output areas are excluded. Legitimate
upstream and fetched executable modes and symlinks are preserved.

The generated .cargo/config.toml uses the relative vendor/cargo path. The build
note gives Zig 0.15.2 offline-cache environment variables and the offline Cargo
command. See OPENHARNESS-CORRESPONDING-SOURCE.md inside the bundle for exact
fetch flags and metadata normalization. No claim of byte-identical binary
reproducibility is made.

This source access information covers the included unmodified Herdr component,
not Open Harness or other separate works aggregated in the container image.
The full AGPL-3.0-or-later text is at /usr/share/doc/herdr/LICENSE. Herdr and
its source are provided without warranty, to the extent permitted by applicable
law.
